Brute Force - using StringBuilder to modify the string with no space, no digit, no uppercase letter, then compare it with "equals"
              Builtin a function to get the desired result.
class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        // StringBuilder to store only lowercase alphanumeric characters
        StringBuilder newStr = new StringBuilder();
        // Iterate through each character of the input string
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            // Check if the character is a letter or digit
            if (Character.isLetterOrDigit(c)) {
                // Convert character to lowercase and append to StringBuilder
                newStr.append(Character.toLowerCase(c));
            }
        }
        // Convert StringBuilder to String and compare it
        // with its reversed version to check palindrome
        return newStr.toString().equals(newStr.reverse().toString());
    }
}

Time Complexity :- O(N).
Space Complexity :- O(1).

Optimal solution - using two pointer technique with skipping letter and digit, and convert string to all lowercase, then just shrink the 
                    to centre and return true if its palindrome.

class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        // Edge case: if the string is empty, it is a valid palindrome
        if (s.isEmpty())
            return true;
        // Initialize two pointers
        // 'start' begins from the start of the string
        // 'end' begins from the end of the string
        int start = 0;
        int end = s.length() - 1;
        // Continue checking characters while start pointer is before end pointer
        while (start < end) {
            // Character at the start pointer
            char cur = s.charAt(start);
            // Character at the end pointer
            char last = s.charAt(end);
            // If the start character is NOT alphanumeric, skip it
            if (!Character.isLetterOrDigit(cur))
                start++;
            // If the end character is NOT alphanumeric, skip it
            else if (!Character.isLetterOrDigit(last))
                end--;
            // If both characters are alphanumeric
            else {
                // Compare characters in lowercase (case-insensitive comparison)
                if (Character.toLowerCase(cur) != Character.toLowerCase(last)) {
                    // If characters do not match, it is not a palindrome
                    return false;
                }
                // Move both pointers inward after successful comparison
                start++;
                end--;
            }
        }
        // If all character comparisons pass, it is a palindrome
        return true;
    }
}

Time Complexity :- O(N).
Space Complexity :- O(1).
